data.meta_description: 23-oct-2023 - Newcastle, County Down, Northern Ireland, is a small seaside resort town known for its sandy beach, forests and mountains. The Mourne Mountains lie south of the town and the local area includes the Tollymore Forest Park and Donard Park. The Shimna River flows through Tollymore Park and enters the sea at Newcastle. Widows' Row is a listed terrace of twelve small houses built in 1843.
